commit.message:
Add explicit LICENSE modified according to
  https://wiki.python.org/moin/PythonSoftwareFoundationLicenseFaq
"How do I use the PSF license?"
Update to working url yet again ...
Update setup.py, CHANGELOG, and spf.py for new version and changes to requires.
Update README.md
Drop support for ipaddr, use ipaddress.collapse_addresses()
Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/sdgathman/pyspf
Update urls
Add doctest to test i='list' to demonstrate the issue from https://github.com/sdgathman/pyspf/issues/24
Add .pyc and __pycache__ to .gitignore
Switch to setuptools because "it's the future"
Add .gitignore so we don't worry about egg-info and dist/ in the repository
Make some RST compatibility changes to README.md
Merge branch 'pyspf-2_0-branch' of https://github.com/sdgathman/pyspf into pyspf-2_0-branch
Support iplist for literal policy.
Update Installation section of README.md
Mention testspf.py works with pyyaml 5.1.2 in comments
Add missing use of timeout parameter for dnspython DNSLookup
Include new README format
Release 2.0.14
Restore DNSLookup API for pydnsv(DNS) for tcp fallback works again

Fix dnspython integration so that SPF TempError is properly raised when
    there are timeout or no nameserver errors
